You can join the game by clicking on the glowing portal over there, which will transport you to your team area. You will be given an amount of gold to start with, based on your total item cost and the game item cost restriction settings.
You cannot join the game until your total item cost is below the set item cost limit of: <CUSTOM500>gp.
You can decrease your total item cost by dropping items, from both your item repository and your equipped inventory.

The Contest Of Champions is a Party Based PvP module, where you compete against other adventurers in grand duels to the death. You are awarded gold for killing other players, which you can use to purchase equipment and other assorted items.

Combatants are required to check in once in the main team area. Once each team has been locked the battle can begin, and will continue until all members of one team have died, respawned or have dropped below one hit point.
Combatants that drop below one hit point begin bleeding. If healed by a teammate before they reach -10 hit points, they can resume fighting.
All spell effects will be removed from you when you enter the arena. I suggest that you rest before checking in and then wait until the battle begins to cast spells.
If you rest after you have checked in, you will be automatically checked out.
Each round the winning team is awarded a variable amount of gold based on the size of the opposing team. If one team wins five times they will be declared the winners of the match.
To "Check In" simply speak with a Fight Master in your team area and he will check you in for the next round of battle.
